<subSubSection id="8231ED59E28D1F9F4008A4EA38698380" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="05B4B38628FCE6CBAE69DAC659490072" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5F56A59C2261937DCD399C32F7F088DA" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Endemic to 
<normalizedToken id="3ED1245975C2FC43FA0F49D60A7D16E2" originalValue="Querétaro">Queretaro</normalizedToken>
in Mexico, where it grows in dry pine and oak woodland at 2200 m on rocky limestone soil.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B63FDFF9E9E06C159E6D8C4C52EF4378" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="5E1C4743652C8ECA85CAF14CDDB9463C" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
MEXICO. 
<normalizedToken id="D397EC92A30F7ED48282D087F2AE6F78" originalValue="Querétaro">Queretaro</normalizedToken>
</emphasis>
