<subSubSection id="343AAA41409A3A05E21AA72E2CA6F260" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="353BEE478C88ABD0F376BD602504CC94" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2E2184B097CA028731E64204CE836CB0" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The distinct 3-lobed, discolorous leaves, very long peduncles, acuminate, aristate sepals with prominent scarious margins and the reddish-purple pubescent corolla mark out this species. There is a strong, probably superficial, resemblance to 
<taxonomicName id="B576438B77865CFA5C2E2CCE46F426D5" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="spruceana">
<emphasis id="568B11F0A01ADD3D96ECCB79B49D7864" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea spruceana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the leaf shape and colouring, inflorescence structure and sepal shape but the shortly pubescent indumentum is very different from the pilose inflorescence of 
<emphasis id="B559E13356CF169363B8E72E3FCEBCC0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="94B60D2D051A20BDC3FC17DF3CAA6B83" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="spruceana">I. spruceana</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
The placement of 
<taxonomicName id="35671543D1C0F15D326723F0063EB49D" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="calcicola">
<emphasis id="6C1879A00540D8DB9D14B315CFBC62AD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">I. calcicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is uncertain and its inclusion here is based on its similarity with 
<taxonomicName id="1BA87515117AD4DB5B1B01BC49D3941F" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="spruceana">
<emphasis id="68E46CAA51A376D2CD5B8D14A8A8EA9D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">I. spruceana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
